+    /// A `ReadOnly<T>` disables any interior mutability in `T`, ensuring that
+    /// a `&ReadOnly<T>` is genuinely read-only. Thus, `ReadOnly<T>` is
+    /// [`Immutable`] regardless of whether `T` is.
+    ///
